result.name: Market Sea

reviews.text: Classic 3 star, the food is impressive, such as the pork neck and the chargrilled platter. One area for improvement in the platter however would be no tomato, this isn’t a British Breakfast, just include more of that beef or lamb skewer, which was incredibly tasty. The service leaves much to be improved and the main reason for the 3 star, it’s IFC you expect a level of service, not to have to call the waiter over constantly, get delivered other peoples dishes by error, and only being offered the second round of your happy hour beer upon request after the bill is delivered and you are reminded by the odd inconsistencies in pricing on it. Again a classic 3 star.

I wished I have known this place earlier so I’d have come often when I visit IFC. This is a Southeast Asian restaurant on the 3rd floor of IFC. You can access from the mall or the outdoor terrace. It offers nice view with great outdoor atmosphere (except it’s too dark at night). It’s a self-served restaurant meaning you have to go to the cashier and order the food yourself but the waitress will bring you the food so there’s no service charge. I wasn’t expecting much but turned out the food is quite good! I really love the fresh mango and beetroot rolls and the mushroom curry with roti. The curry is definitely tasty and just perfect with roti and rice. I didn’t order much cause I’m afraid it’s not gonna be authentic but I’ll definitely come back and try out more. It’s definitely a perfect place to hang out with friends with such a nice view and large table. I’m taking one star off because the service is quite slow and it took a while to wait at the cashier and took another while to wait for the cashier to figure out how to actually use the system. The price is reasonable given the location.

Nice food very good taste!  Waitresses and waiters were considerate, providing signature dishes suggestions and reminded us the need of dessert.  Of course this should not be a surprise for this class of restaurants in IFC.  Yet they didn't refill our water automatically.  We had to asked them.  Virtually they were short of waiters.

Quite a good choice for lunch in Central. Staff are nice. Food is delicious. Seafood curry is great! The only not good point is one hour limit time for lunch, but such arrangement is common in Central's restaurants.
Eye catching delicacy with decent environment. Price around $200 per person for dinner.

result.name: ifc mall

reviews.text: ifc is probably one of the best malls in Hong Kong. With the wide variety of food and the even wider variety of clothing, this makes the mall a comfortable and one of the best malls. The train station is also located near the mall for easier access and convenient travel. Would definitely recommend to tourists and travelers.

Huge open shopping mall with plenty of restaurants and great connections throughout Hong Kong be they ferry, train, buses or even the airport express. There are plenty of open areas, including the rooftop area which is reserved for restaurants and bars. The area has a luxury vibe at a corresponding price tag.
Probably one of my favorite malls in the world. You can find here basically anything, from Shake Shack, to cold-pressed juices, clothing stores, Apple, electronics and much more.

Hong Kong is full of places like this. Shopping mall stuffed with expensive brands, an Apple store and a cinema. There is a city super and if you want a decent coffee go to fuel. It also has a music shop with a pretty good selection of new vinyl. Best thing to do here? Buy some beers from city super or nearby marks and Spencers and head up to the Mall roof top garden and watch Kowloon as the sun goes down, or a storm is coming in. Pretty awesome.
Excellent mall, just above the Hong Kong train station. Has excellent options for shopping and food which includes all varieties. Overall excellent place.
